---
name: scljet-typedsql-dml
description: SclJet typed SQL writes — INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE built from typed combinators; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet typed SQL writes

Extends the typed surface to writes: `insertRows`, `updateSet` with typed `setInt`/`setText`/`setExpr`
assignments (the value/expr type must match the column type), and `deleteWhere`, each erasing to the
existing `InsertStmt`/`UpdateStmt`/`DeleteStmt` and running through the same executor. The new image
threads through the sequence and each read-after-write is checked against reference sqlite3 running
the equivalent SQL (verified out-of-band); locked across `[int, js]`.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)
[Table, Column, IntType, TextType, col, colExpr, intLit, plus, eqp, gep, setText, setExpr, insertRows, updateSet, deleteWhere, runInsert, runUpdate, runDelete, from, selectStar, orderByQ, orderAsc, runTypedQuery](std/scljet/typedsql.ssc)

```scalascript
val emp: Table = Table("emp", List("id", "name", "salary"))
val cId: Column[Long] = col("emp", "id", 0, IntType)
val cName: Column[String] = col("emp", "name", 1, TextType)
val cSalary: Column[Long] = col("emp", "salary", 2, IntType)

def dumpAll(db: ByteSlice, tag: String): Unit =
  runTypedQuery(db, orderByQ(selectStar(from(emp)), orderAsc(cId) :: Nil)) match
    case Left(m) => println(tag + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(tag + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, salary INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(100L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(250L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat"), SqlInteger(300L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    runInsert(db0, insertRows(emp,
      List(List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(150L)),
           List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("eve"), SqlInteger(500L))))) match
      case Left(m) => println("afterInsert => ERR:" + m)
      case Right(db1) =>
        dumpAll(db1, "afterInsert")
        runUpdate(db1, updateSet(emp, setExpr(cSalary, plus(colExpr(cSalary), intLit(10L))) :: Nil, eqp(cId, intLit(1L)))) match
          case Left(m) => println("upd1 => ERR:" + m)
          case Right(db2) =>
            runUpdate(db2, updateSet(emp, setText(cName, "BOB") :: Nil, eqp(cId, intLit(2L)))) match
              case Left(m) => println("upd2 => ERR:" + m)
              case Right(db3) =>
                dumpAll(db3, "afterUpdate")
                runDelete(db3, deleteWhere(emp, gep(cSalary, intLit(300L)))) match
                  case Left(m) => println("del => ERR:" + m)
                  case Right(db4) => dumpAll(db4, "afterDelete")
```
